  • Method Details

    • create

      public SpaceObject create(Map<String,String> data)
      Creates a new Unknown object using the provided data map.
      Specified by:
      create in class SpaceObjectFactory
      Parameters:
      data - A map containing the data required to create an Unknown object. The map should include the following keys:
      • record_id - The unique identifier for the unknown object.
      • satellite_name - The name of the satellite associated with the unknown object.
      • country - The country responsible for the unknown object.
      • approximate_orbit_type - The type of orbit the unknown object is in.
      • launch_year - The year the unknown object was launched.
      • launch_site - The site where the unknown object was launched.
      • longitude - The longitude of the unknown object.
      • avg_longitude - The average longitude of the unknown object.
      • geohash - The geohash location of the unknown object.
      • days_old - The age of the unknown object in days.
      • conjunction_count - The number of conjunction events involving the unknown object.
      Returns:
      A new Unknown object populated with the provided data.
